Vice President Mike Pence addressed soldiers and their families at U.S. Army Garrison Yongsan in Seoul, South Korea on Easter Sunday. He expressed gratitude for their service and assured them that President Trump is committed to rebuilding the military and providing the resources needed to accomplish their missions. Pence also emphasized the strong alliance between the United States and South Korea, stating that freedom will prevail on the Korean peninsula. He shared a personal story about his father, who served in the Korean War, and expressed admiration for the courage and valor of the soldiers present. Pence's wife, Karen, led a prayer before the meal, thanking God for the sacrifices made by military families and asking for blessings on the soldiers and the country.